Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, March 26 (KPL) -- Lao Prime Minister 
Khamtai Siphandon, at yesterday afternoon's meeting with State 
Minister, Minister of Social Welfare, Health and Towns Mrs. 
Simone Veil, highly assessed the visit to Laos by the French 
Government's member and hoped that her visit would contribute to 
further enhancing the bilateral relations of friendship and 
cooperation between the two countries. 
  Mr. Khamtai Siphandon hoped that her visit, despite being 
brief, would give the minister a better insight of the country 
as it was implementing the policy of renovation. The Lao prime 
minister wished that her visit to Laos would be fruitful for the 
benefits of both sides. 
  Yesterday afternoon, Mrs. Simone Veil visited the Mahosot 
hospital and had an exchange of views on health issue with 
officials of the hospital. 

